OL,3,CHow Clare's Law can help prevent
OL,4,Cdomestic abuse in Jersey
OL,6,FAny member of the public can make a
OL,7,Fdisclosure application if they believe
OL,8,Fto be at risk of domestic abuse from a
OL,9,Fcurrent or ex-partner, are worried
OL,10,Fabout someone they know or are a
OL,11,Fprofessional and have information that
OL,12,Fsuggests someone could be at risk of
OL,13,Fdomestic abuse.
OL,15,FDetective Superintendent Alison Fossey
OL,16,Fsays: "We want to save lives and we
OL,17,Falso want to prevent and reduce
OL,18,Fdomestic abuse, so this law really
OL,19,Ftargets serial perpetrators as we know
OL,20,Fthey often move from one victim to
OL,21,Fanother.
